Most travelers assume check-in counters operate consistently throughout the day. Having coordinated with airline operations, I learned that counter staffing follows patterns that create bottlenecks at surprising times.

The **[reliable airport transportation](https://expresscoloradotransportation.com/town-car-service-to-dia/)** services that understand airport operations know that airline counter staffing changes create predictable delays. For example, most airlines reduce counter staff between 10 AM-2 PM, assuming most passengers will use self-service options. However, during peak travel periods, this leads to longer lines for passengers who need special assistance or have complex check-in requirements.

